23/11/2008
PODGORICA, Montenegro -- Police in the port town of Bar have seized 13kg of explosives, local media reported on Saturday (November 22nd). 
It happened during a car check in a joint operation by police forces from Podgorica and Niksic. 
Police officers found 65 packages of TNT in the vehicle. 
They arrested two people in the car.
In other news, the Bulgarian customs agency said on Friday authorities incinerated 180kg of illegal drugs seized at the country's border checkpoints and in police raids. 
The drugs included large stashes of heroin, amphetamines and marijuana. 
(Pobjeda, RTCG - 22/11/08; AP, AFP, BTA, BNR, Makfax - 21/11/08)
